current-chamber.#text: IN THE SENATE OF THE UNITED STATES

official-title.#text:
Commemorating the 150th anniversary of Emporia State
		  University.

cosponsor.#tail:
) submitted the following
			 resolution; which was considered and agreed to

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail:
recognizes and
			 extends its congratulations to the educational professionals, students, and
			 alumni of Emporia State University for 150 years of excellence in higher
			 education.

text.#text:
Whereas, in 1863, the State of Kansas founded the Kansas
			 State Normal School to provide opportunities for higher education in the fields
			 of teaching, mechanic arts, agriculture, and various other arts and
			 sciences;

Whereas Emporia State University is the alma mater of more
			 than 75,000 proud alumni; and

Whereas the quality of Emporia State University as an
			 institution of higher learning is a reflection of the extraordinary caliber of
			 its educational professionals and students: Now, therefore, be it

{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}title.#text: 113 SRES 33 ATS: Commemorating the 150th anniversary of Emporia State University.
